      <div class="article-teaser">
        Between Friday 30 March and Monday 2 April, the majority of the transport network is open. If you're travelling in London, make the most of your bank holiday weekend by checking the planned works and events that may affect your journey. You can find travel advice for the Easter weekend here.
        
      </div>
    
    <div class="on-this-page">
      <p><strong>Page last updated: 2 April 2018, 18:45</strong></p>
<p><strong>Essential works on the Northern line may take longer than expected. It is possible that very early Northern line services may be disrupted on Tuesday 3 April.</strong></p>
<p>Check <a href="/status-updates/index">Status updates</a> before you travel on Tuesday morning or follow us on Twitter &#64;northernline for the latest travel information.</p>
<p>If you're travelling in London over the Easter Bank Holiday, closures include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>TfL Rail:</strong> No service on the entire line from Friday until Monday</li>
    <li><strong>London Overground:</strong> No service between
    <ul>
        <li>Romford and Upminster from Friday until Monday</li>
        <li>Liverpool Street and Enfield Town/Cheshunt/Walthamstow Central from Saturday until Monday (closure extends to Chingford on Sunday only until 10:15)</li>
        <li>New Cross Gate and Crystal Palace/West Croydon on Saturday and Sunday</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Northern line:</strong> No service between Charing Cross/Moorgate and Golders Green/East Finchley from Friday until Monday</li>
    <li><strong>Circle and Hammersmith &amp; City lines:</strong> No service between Edgware Road and Hammersmith on Saturday and Sunday</li>
    <li><strong>District line:</strong> No service between Edgware Road and High Street Kensington on Saturday and Sunday</li>
    <li><strong>London Trams:</strong> No service between Sandilands and Reeves Corner from Friday until Wednesday 4 April (closure changes to Sandilands to East Croydon from Thursday 5 April until Sunday 8 April).</li>
    <li><strong>National Rail:</strong> Planned works will affect services, including to and from Heathrow, Euston, Liverpool Street, London Bridge, Moorgate, Paddington and Waterloo</li>
</ul>
<p>Other travel changes include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Driving: </strong>No Congestion Charge or T-Charge from Friday to Monday</li>
    <li><strong>Buses:</strong> Amended timetable for Friday and Monday</li>
    <li><strong>DLR: </strong>A Saturday service will run on Friday, Saturday and Monday</li>
</ul>
<p>Thursday 29 March is also expected to be busy in and around London.</p>
<ul>
</ul>
      
           
      
