<h2>TfL Rail</h2>
<p>There's no service on the entire line from Friday 30 March until Monday 2 April while Network Rail carries out track and station improvements including Crossrail construction work.<br />
<br />
Please use the Central line between Liverpool Street and Stratford. Rail replacement buses will also run between:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Stratford City and Romford calling at Forest Gate, Manor Park, Ilford, Seven Kings, Goodmayes and Chadwell Heath (approx. every 10 minutes)</li>
    <li>Newbury Park (for the Central line) and Shenfield calling at Chadwell Heath, Romford, Gidea Park, Harold Wood and Brentwood (approx. every 15 minutes)</li>
</ul>
<p>For live information on TfL Rail, see our <a href="/status-updates/index">status updates</a> page or <a href="https://twitter.com/tflrail">follow &#64;TfLRail on Twitter</a>.</p>
<hr />
<h2>London Overground</h2>
<ul>
    <li>No service between Romford and Upminster from Friday 30 March until Monday 2 April due to Crossrail construction work and Network Rail infrastructure work. Please use local bus routes:
    <ul>
        <li> 165 Romford - Emerson Park (approx. every 10-20 mins)</li>
        <li> 248 Romford - Upminster (approx. every 7-20 mins)</li>
        <li> 370 Romford - Emerson Park - Upminster (approx. every 15-30 mins)</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>No service between Liverpool Street and Enfield Town/Cheshunt/Walthamstow Central from Saturday 31 March to Monday 2 April (extends to Chingford on Sunday 1 April until approximately 10:15). This is due to Network Rail track and infrastructure work and station improvement works at White Hart Lane
    <ul>
        <li>Please use alternative Tube or local bus routes. Rail replacement buses will also run approximately every 15-30 minutes to each destination:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service L1:</strong> Seven Sisters to Enfield Town calling at Bruce Grove, White Hart Lane, Silver Street, Edmonton Green and Bush Hill Park</li>
            <li><strong>Service L2:</strong> Seven Sister to Cheshunt calling at Bruce Grove, White Hart Lane, Silver Street, Edmonton Green, Bush Hill Park, Southbury, Turkey Street and Theobalds Grove</li>
            <li><strong>Service L3:</strong> Hackney Downs to Walthamstow Central calling at Clapton and St James Street (continues to Wood Street, Highams Park and Chingford on Sunday until approximately 10:15)</li>
        </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>No service between New Cross Gate and Crystal Palace/West Croydon on Saturday 31 March and Sunday 1 April due to Network Rail track and infrastructure work
    <ul>
        <li>Rail replacement buses will run approximately every 10 minutes:
        <ul>
            <li>New Cross Gate to West Croydon calling at Brockley, Honor Oak Park, Forest Hill, Sydenham, Crystal Palace, Anerley (walk to/from Penge West), Norwood Junction and Selhurst</li>
        </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>Service changes</h3>
<p>Routes affected by closures:</p>
<ul>
    <li>An amended Saturday service will run on Friday, Saturday and Monday. An amended Sunday service will run on Sunday</li>
</ul>
<p>Routes without closures:</p>
<ul>
    <li>An amended Saturday service will run on Friday and Monday</li>
    <li>A Saturday service will run on Saturday </li>
    <li>A Sunday service will run on Sunday</li>
</ul>
<p>For live information on London Overground, see our <a href="/status-updates/index">status updates</a> page or <a href="https://twitter.com/ldnoverground">follow &#64;LDNOverground on Twitter</a>.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Tube</h2>
<h3>Circle line and Hammersmith &amp; City lines: Saturday 31 March and Sunday 1 April</h3>
<ul>
    <li>There's no service between Edgware Road and Hammersmith on the Circle line and Hammersmith &amp; City lines while we test new signalling. Please use alternative Tube and local bus routes.</li>
</ul>
<h3>District line: Saturday 31 March and Sunday 1 April</h3>
<ul>
    <li>There's no service between Edgware Road and High Street Kensington while we test new signalling. Please use alternative Tube and local bus routes.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Northern line: Friday 30 March - Monday 2 April</h3>
<ul>
    <li>There's no service between Charing Cross/Moorgate and Golders Green/East Finchley while we carry out points works at Camden Town. Please use alternative Tube, bus or rail replacement bus services.</li>
</ul>
<p>Rail replacement buses will run between:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Euston and Finchley Road (for the Jubilee line) calling at Mornington Crescent, Camden Town, Chalk Farm, Belsize Park, Hampstead and Golders Green (approx. every 4 minutes)</li>
    <li>King's Cross St Pancras and Finchley Central calling at Camden Town, Kentish Town, Tufnell Park, Archway, Highgate and East Finchley (approx. every 8 minutes)</li>
</ul>
<p>Also, on Tuesday 3 and Wednesday 4 April, all southbound Northern line trains from Edgware will be via Charing Cross and all trains from High Barnet and Mill Hill East will be via Bank. </p>
<p>For up-to-date information on Tube services <a href="https://twitter.com/TfLTravelAlerts">follow &#64;TfLTravelAlerts </a>or visit TfL's<a href="/travel-information/social-media-and-email-updates/index"> individual Tube line accounts </a>for real-time information.</p>
<hr />
<h2>London Trams</h2>
<p>There's no service between Sandilands and Reeves Corner from Friday 30 March to Wednesday 4 April while we carry out track renewal work.</p>
<p> Please use local bus routes or the express rail replacement buses which will run approximately every 8-10 minutes between Sandilands and Waddon Marsh calling at Vicarage Road (for Wandle Park)</p>
<p>From Thursday 5 until Sunday 8 April, there is no service between Sandilands and East Croydon. Please use local bus routes.</p>
<p>For the latest information on how trams are running, visit our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/">status updates page </a>or <a href="http://www.twitter.com/tramslondon">follow &#64;TramsLondon </a>on Twitter.</p>
<hr />
