<h2>Driving</h2>

<ul>
	<li>There will be no Congestion Charge or T-Charge from Friday 30 March until&nbsp;Monday 2 April.</li>
	<li>Planned works mean there will be traffic diversions in central London. Please allow extra time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Camden High Street closure</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Camden High Street will be closed between the junctions of the A400, Kentish Town Road and Inverness Street, while maintenance works are carried out at Camden Town Station.<br />
	This closure will take place from Thursday 29 March at 22:00 to Tuesday 3 April at 06:00. A signed diversion route will be in place. However some delays are expected so please allow more time for your journey.<br />
	Parking suspensions will be enforced at various locations from 17:30 Thursday 29 March through to 06:00 Tuesday 3 April.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Baker Street&nbsp;two-way</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Works are taking place to <a href="/travel-information/improvements-and-projects/baker-street">convert Baker Street and Gloucester Place to two-way traffic</a>. One lane in each direction will be closed along Marylebone Road (between the junctions with Balcombe Street and Baker Street) until May 2018.</li>
</ul>

<h3>West End project</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Works are set to begin to convert Tottenham Court Road and Gower Street to two-way traffic. <a href="/status-updates/index">Status updates here</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Wigmore Street</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Work to improve Wigmore Street for pedestrians and cyclists is underway. Six junctions will be improved with upgraded pedestrian crossings, advanced stop lines for cyclists and where possible widened footways.</li>
</ul>

<p>For the latest information on traffic conditions, see our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/traffic/status/">traffic status updates page</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/tfltrafficnews">follow &#64;TfLTrafficNews on Twitter</a>.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Buses</h2>

<p>On Friday 30 March and Monday 2 April, buses will run to a different timetable.</p>

<ul>
	<li>Friday &#45; Saturday service</li>
	<li>Saturday &#45; normal (Saturday) service</li>
	<li>Sunday &#45; normal (Sunday) service</li>
	<li>Monday &#45; Sunday service</li>
</ul>

<p>For the latest information on how buses are running, see our <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/bus/status/">bus status updates</a> or follow <a href="https://twitter.com/TfLBusAlerts">&#64;TfLBusAlerts on Twitter</a>.</p>

<hr />
<h2>DLR</h2>

<ul>
	<li>A Saturday service will run on Friday, Saturday and Monday</li>
	<li>On Sunday, a normal Sunday service will run</li>
</ul>

<p>For live information on DLR, see our <a href="/status-updates/index">status updates</a> page or <a href="https://twitter.com/londonDLR">follow &#64;LondonDLR on Twitter</a>.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Cycling</h2>

<p>Santander Cycles will be available throughout the Easter Bank Holiday.</p>

<p>The following docking stations will be out of service for works:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Smugglers Way</li>
	<li>Flood Street</li>
	<li>Drummond Street</li>
	<li>Foley Street, Fitzrovia</li>
	<li>Bourne Street, Belgravia</li>
	<li>Clifford Street, Mayfair</li>
	<li>Portugal Street, Holborn</li>
	<li>Moor Street, Soho</li>
	<li>Westfield Eastern Access Road, Shepherd's Bush (long-term)</li>
	<li>Rodney Street, Angel (long-term)</li>
	<li>South Quay West, Canary Wharf (long-term)</li>
</ul>

<p>Check availability of Santander Cycles using the <a href="/modes/cycling/santander-cycles/find-a-docking-station">online docking station map</a>, or download Santander Cycles from the <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/gb/app/santander-cycles/id974792287?mt=8">App Store</a> or <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=uk.gov.tfl.cyclehire&amp;hl=en_GB">Google Play</a>. Follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/santandercycles">&#64;SantanderCycles on Twitter </a>for the latest updates.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Coaches</h2>

<p>Services are expected to be very busy, so advance booking is strongly recommended. Please check the timetable of your service with your service operator. Get the <a href="/modes/coaches/coach-companies">full list of coach operators</a>.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Dial-a-Ride</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Regular bookings will not run on Good Friday and Easter Monday but if you still wish to travel, please make a one-off booking</li>
</ul>

<p>Full details of Easter booking arrangements are available on the<a href="/modes/dial-a-ride/index"> Dial-a-Ride page</a>.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Taxis &amp; private hire vehicles</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Taxi (black cabs) and private hire services, including minicabs, will be running throughout Easter. Find out more about taxi&nbsp;<a href="/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/taxi-fares">fares</a>.</li>
	<li><a href="/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/book-a-taxi">Find booking information, i</a>ncluding phone numbers and email addresses,&nbsp;for minicab and other private hire operators in London</li>
</ul>

<p>For up-to-date information, visit our <a href="/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/index">taxis and minicabs section</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/TfLTPH">follow &#64;TfLTPH on Twitter</a>.</p>

<p>Please be aware that planned works and closures on the roads may affect your journey. Visit our<a href="http://tfl.gov.uk/traffic/status/"> live traffic status tool </a>for more information.</p>

<hr />
<h2>Rivers</h2>

<p>The Woolwich Ferry will run a Sunday service on Friday and Monday, and a normal service on Saturday and Sunday.<br />
Thames Clippers will run a weekend service on Friday and Monday, and a normal service on Saturday and Sunday.<br />
<a href="/modes/river/index">Check&nbsp;our river section</a>&nbsp;for more information</p>

<hr />
<h2>Emirates Air Line</h2>

<ul>
	<li>On Friday and Saturday, services will run between 08:00 and 23:00</li>
	<li>On Sunday and Monday, services will run between 09:00 and 22:00</li>
</ul>

<p>Find out more in our <a href="/modes/emirates-air-line/index">Emirates Air Line section</a> or <a href="http://www.twitter.com/emiratesairldn">follow &#64;EmiratesAirLDN </a>on Twitter.</p>

<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
